cache/generation/drafts/image.md:107:For Lottie-backed image content, `Dali::Ui::LottieAnimation::DynamicPropertyInfo` describes a per-frame dynamic property binding. The structure is app-owned while being prepared, and its `callback` ownership is transferred when the dynamic property is applied by the dali-ui Lottie image API.
cache/generation/drafts/image.md:111:- `Dali::Ui::LottieAnimation::DynamicPropertyInfo::id`: an application-defined integer passed back to the callback.
cache/generation/drafts/image.md:112:- `Dali::Ui::LottieAnimation::DynamicPropertyInfo::keyPath`: the target layer or element path.
cache/generation/drafts/image.md:113:- `Dali::Ui::LottieAnimation::DynamicPropertyInfo::property`: the vector property selected for dynamic update.
cache/generation/drafts/image.md:114:- `Dali::Ui::LottieAnimation::DynamicPropertyInfo::callback`: the per-frame value callback.
cache/generation/drafts/image.md:120:void PrepareDynamicImageProperty(Dali::Ui::LottieAnimation::DynamicPropertyInfo& info,
cache/generation/drafts/image.md:129:Use a stable `id` when one callback serves several dynamic image updates. The callback can then branch on `Dali::Ui::LottieAnimation::DynamicPropertyInfo::id` without needing separate callback objects for each target.
